    "(11) and a check needs to be performed.",
    "This polynomialtechnique to determine the solutions of the normalized lens equation is very successfully used in the field of planetary microlensing, where N is only a few (binary, triple system etc, e.g.",
    "Another elegant procedure to find all images corresponding to a point source is due to Witt (1993) (see also Lewis et al. 1993, for a different implementation of the same idea).",
    "Witt (1993) shows that all images of a point source can be found by following a straight source track from far away from the ensemble of point masses to the position of interest ζ:",
    "-For a source position ζ 0 very far away from the ensemble of N point masses there exists one image close to the source and N images close to the masses m i."
